    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="276"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.574/6a supp.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Swenson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-29">May 29,
                            1929</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 462</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s instruction No.
                    442, of December 1, 1928,<note n="40" xml:id="d276fn40">See instruction No. 167,
                        December 1, 1928, to the Ambassador in Belgium, <ref
                            target="frus1928v01#pg_497">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1928, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 497</ref>.</note> in regard to the
                    desired negotiation of a treaty between <pb facs="0608" n="472" xml:id="pg_472"
                    /> the United States and Norway providing that persons born in the United States
                    of Norwegian parentage, and naturalized American citizens, shall not be held
                    liable for military service or any other act of allegiance during a stay in the
                    territory subject to the jurisdiction of the Norwegian Government while citizens
                    of the United States of America under the laws thereof, to which instruction no
                    answer appears to have been received, I have to request a reply thereto as soon
                    as circumstances will permit.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. R. Castile, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
